node.text: The inspiration for this Spicy Tofu and Zucchini Stew that @annie.h.shi makes for cozy weeknight dinners every season of the year comes from Soondubu Jjigae, a spicy Korean tofu stew, that she grew up eating at restaurants. The recipe features an umami-rich broth powered by dashi packets, gochugaru, doenjang (fermented soybean paste), and gochujang. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: “I think this cookie is so elegant and so New York chic and I’m gonna take it to SoHo,” says Chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) as she adds gold leaf to her take on the classic Black and White cookie. Find out how to make them by visiting this link:https://bit.ly/3zD88fk or tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.title: Pastries with Paola | Black and Ruby Cookies

node.text:
Straight from pages of "The Essentials of Classic Italian Cooking" by Marcella Hazan, there is a reason why this Tomato Sauce with Onion and Butter recipe is one of the most popular of all-time. People skip the pasta just to eat the sauce directly out of the pot with a spoon, it's that good. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 
📸: @juliagartland

node.text:
Use up your late-season peaches, plums or nectarines for this hearty Stone Fruit Salad with Collard-Peanut Pesto. Fonio, a West African grain similar in texture to couscous, soaks up the the pesto, imbuing each bite with extra flavor. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!
🥗: @foodculturist 📸: @jesspettway

node.text: Deftly deep frying and dunking are two key steps  @claudetteazepeda completes to make her Homemade Churros With Cajeta on this episode of Chefs At Home. Tap the link in bio to watch the full episode on YouTube!
